         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Tilbury 2 Port Expansion</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>CB/203644</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="45000000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Port of Tilbury London Limited (PoTLL) is seeking Expressions of Interest from suitably accredited and demonstrably experienced contractors to design and build new port facilities for the existing Tilbury port. The purpose of the works is to increase capacity at the port by providing new fixed and floating berthing facilities for the unloading and loading of ships and new hard standings for cargo handling, processing and storage. The works will also include a new rail head, the construction of road and rail links to existing networks, and sundry port facility building works.</P>
               <P>The procurement will be split into two contracts:</P>
               <P>(1) a marine works contract; and</P>
               <P>(2) a terrestrial works contract.</P>
               <P>Interested parties are asked to click "Record Your Interest Now" and submit a message via the portal indicating whether they intend to submit a bid for Lot 1 or Lot 2 or both Lots 1 and 2.</P>
               <P>The estimated date of publication of the contract notice is 22.3.2018, although this is subject to change.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">80000000</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Marine Works</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>1</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45213342"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45241000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45241100"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45244000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKH32"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Land at the former Tilbury Power Station, Tilbury, Essex RM18 8UJ.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Marine Works contract comprising all works within the tidal estuary beyond the existing sea wall/flood defences including the floating pontoon, articulated bridge, fenders, dolphins and associated pilings, river bed preparation and option(s) for RoRo (Roll-on/Roll-off) approach bridge link and Construction Materials and Aggregates Terminal (CMAT) berth.</P>
                  <P>The floating berthing facility will allow for two RoRo ships, with an additional berth for bulk materials ships.</P>
                  <P>The marine works will be constructed within the tidal estuary of the River Thames.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="2">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Terrestrial Works</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>2</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45200000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45220000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45222000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45240000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKH32"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Land at the former Tilbury Power Station, Tilbury, Essex RM18 8UJ.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Terrestrial Works contract comprising all works landside of the existing sea wall/flood defences including RoRo (Roll-on / Roll-off) terminal and enabling works for a Construction Materials and Aggregates Terminal (CMAT), all paving and hard standings, adoptable highway works, relocation of existing railhead and laying of new rail facilities, workshops, security facilities, fencing, controlled vehicle and pedestrian access points, and option for RoRo approach bridge link.</P>
                  <P>The terrestrial port facility works will occupy the site of an old, and previously demolished coal fired power station, with the road and rail links to the existing network taking place on land currently used for the storage of vehicles and green fields.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-03-22</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>PoTLL has submitted an application to the UK Planning Inspectorate (acting on behalf of the Secretaries of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government and for Transport) for development consent for the project under the Planning Act 2008. If granted, this will be in the form of a Development Consent Order (DCO). The application for the DCO was submitted on 31st October 2017 and final determination of the application is expected in February 2019.</P>
               <P>The procurement will be split into two contracts: (1) a marine works contract, and (2) a terrestrial works contract. Interested parties are asked to click "Record Your Interest Now" and submit a message via the portal indicating whether they will be submitting a bid for Lot 1, Lot 2 or both Lots 1 and 2.</P>
               <P>Failure to submit an Expression of Interest will not preclude parties from future participation in this procurement. The Expression of Interest and associated message are merely to provide PoTLL with an early indication of market interest.</P>
               <P>The estimated date of publication of the contract notice is 22/03/2018, although this is subject to change.</P>
               <P>PoTLL are looking to engage contractor(s) on fixed price design and build contracts using the Infrastructure Conditions of Contract (ICC) terms and conditions incorporating PoTLL specific amendments.</P>
               <P>Additional information regarding this project can be found at:</P>
               <P>https://www.tilbury2.co.uk/</P>
               <P>https://infrastructure.planninginspectorate.gov.uk/projects/south-east/tilbury2/</P>
               <P>NOTE: To register your interest in this notice and obtain any additional information please visit the myTenders Web Site at http://www.myTenders.org/Search/Search_Switch.aspx?ID=208135.</P>
               <P>(MT Ref:208135).</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-02-22</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
